   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, July 12, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Stuart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   DIPLOMAT-JAILED (Los Angeles) _ The arrest in a drunk-driving
case of the consul general at the Republic of Guatemala's L.A.
mission has once again raised the extent to which foreign
dignitaries may exercise their diplomatic immunity in the United
States. By Peter Hartlaub. (Will move in the ``n'' California news
file and the ``a'' national news file.)
</P>
