<HEADLINE>
SEC OFFICIAL JOINING NEW YORK LAW FIRM 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Colleen Mahoney, acting general counsel at the Securities and
Exchange Commission and a former deputy enforcement director,
disclosed this week that upon leaving the commission she would
become a partner handling securities and litigation matters at the
New York law firm of Skadden, Arps, Slate, Meagher &AMP; Flom.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Mahoney announced in March that she would be leaving the
commission for a job with a private firm.
</P>
<P>
   In her 15 years at the SEC, Ms. Mahoney also worked as executive
assistant to Arthur Levitt, the commission's chairman; chief
counsel of the commission's enforcement division, and assistant
general counsel.
</P>
<P>
   ``The SEC, the securities markets and countless investors are
all better off because of Colleen's keen sense of fairness,
intellectual abilities and relentless pursuit of justice,'' Levitt
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
