<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKL-SPARKS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ROCKERS TO VISIT FORUM
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By PAMELA LEWIS  
 c.1998 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Sparks hope to get back to the business of winning today as
they play host to Cleveland Rockers at 1 p.m. at the Forum.
</P>
<P>
   The Sparks (3-8) returned to the basement for the second time
this season Wednesday after shooting 36 percent, losing to the
Sacramento Monarchs, 76-71, for the third time.
</P>
<P>
   Despite the loss, center Pamela McGee had perhaps her best game
with the Sparks, scoring 16 points and grabbing nine rebounds,
which would be a positive sign for the Sparks should she continue
in the same manner.
</P>
<P>
   The Rockers, who opened the season 4-1, fell to 6-6 after
losing, 76-60, to the Phoenix Mercury Friday. Leading a balanced
attack for Cleveland are Isabelle Fijalkowski and Janice Braxton,
who average 12.1 points per game each. Suzie McConnell-Serio, a
former Olympian who returned to the hard court after a six-year
layoff and four children later, leads the WNBA in assists with 6.8.
</P>
<P>
   The Sparks were 2-2 against Cleveland last season.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By The PRESS TELEGRAM, LONG BEACH, CALIFORNIA
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
